==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skirret
<hw>Skir"ret</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A corrupted form
equivalent to <ets>sugarwort</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An
umbelliferous plant (<spn>Sium Sisarum</spn> syn. <spn>Pimpinella
Sisarum</spn>). It is a native of Asia, but has been long cultivated in
Europe for its edible clustered tuberous roots, which are very
sweet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skirrhus</ent>⟦br⟧
